N2  - Deep Brain Stimulation (DBS) is being used to modulate the activity of motor and limbic circuits in the treatment of movement disorders and psychiatric illness. More recently, we have applied DBS in the fornix to study its effects in the context of a clinical trial or Alzheimer's disease. We have noted that the delivery of electrical stimulation here can produce striking clinical effects including in some cases, memory-related phenomenon. The rationale and preliminary observations seen with hypothalamic/ fornix stimulation in our clinical trial for Alzheimer's disease and in animal models will be reviewed.
