N2  - The proceedings contain 1225 papers. The topics discussed include: buprenorphine: the science of its development to clinical use; developing a novel glutamatergic anti-depressant: the story of GLYX-13; biophysical foundations of transcranial direct current stimulation (tDCS): evidence from computer models and animal studies; translational use of tDCS in major depressive disorder: focus on neuroplasticity; tDCS as an add-on therapy: the augmentative role of tDCS for the treatment of depression; cortical vs subcortical D1 dopamine receptor function and D1-glutamate interactions in schizophrenia-related phenotypic effects: mutant mouse models; a proof of concept, randomized clinical trial of DAR-0100A for cognitive deficits in schizophrenia; sex differences in cocaine-induced brain activation in cocaine sensitized rats; allosteric modulators of GPCRs for treatment of CNS disorders: assessing target-engagement; and effects of lisdexamfetamine (Vyvanse®) on reward processing.
